               <p>SARAH BAVIS. I <rs id="t18260914-291-viclabel1648" type="occupation">keep a shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-291-victim1582 t18260914-291-viclabel1648"></join> in <placeName id="t18260914-291-crimeloc1649">Paul-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-291-crimeloc1649" type="placeName" value="Paul-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260914-291-crimeloc1649" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260914-291-off1645 t18260914-291-crimeloc1649"></join>. On the 15th of July, between two and three o'clock, I saw the prisoner standing at my shop door while I was in the yard- I ran up to him, and he asked if I had got any peppermint drops; I said I believed I had - I turned, and he ran off; I pursued him, but lost sight of him; a young man pursued, and brought him back in a few minutes; I went back, locked my door, and went to Willow-street, where I met the young man coming back with the shoes and the prisoner - these are them; they were missing. I sell shoes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-291-person1583">
                  JOHN 
                  WHITE
               <interp inst="t18260914-291-person1583" type="surname" value="WHITE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-291-person1583" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260914-291-person1583" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard a call of Stop thief! I ran down Willow-court, and took the prisoner; the moment I took him I saw the shoes laying by his side - he said "It is not me."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-291-person1584">
